    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Shelves or the Web?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marsha J Shapiro letter notes sharp competition on line in sale of old books (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I am a book dealer who has been a member of the Advanced Book Exchange (abebooks.com) for nearly three years and beg to differ with you about higher prices. As a book dealer (Marsha J. Shapiro Books), I am now forced to check the price of every book I intend to list. If I wish to sell my copy, I must price it at least $l or more below the least expensive copy listed. The researchers in the study you mentioned are obviously not aware of the severe competition in the field of old, used and rare books.</p>
        <p>MARSHA J.SHAPIRO  New York City</p>
      </block>
